description: 2 x Maples - Reduce entire trees down to a height of 6 metres1 x Large Maple - Crown reduce height and spread by 25%, Crown thin 15%, (remove broken branch and deadwood)1 x Oak - Remove one low branch and reduce extremities as depicted in photographs 1 and 2 received 28th July 2015, (remove deadwood)1 x Oak - Reduce extremities as depicted in photograph 3 received 28th July 2015, (remove deadwood)All standing in area A1 of Tree Preservation Order
